# Context Passing

Every delegation must use an explicit packet.

## Required packet fields

- `goal`
- `why_now`
- `scope`
- `inputs`
- `constraints`
- `reference_boundary`
- `expected_output`
- `stop_conditions`
- `follow_on_hints`

## Rules

- Do not delegate vague work.
- Do not omit writable vs read-only boundaries.
- Keep packets small enough that the agent can act immediately.
- If the packet is unclear, tighten it before delegation.
- Include `tracking` only when the runtime actually intends to aggregate slice costs.
